// Golden-image probe for the post-process tonemapping pipeline: the `tonemapping`
// example renders an `Hdr` camera through the full HDR-intermediate path (environment
// map lighting, test-pattern glTF scenes, default `TonyMcMapface`), so any change to
// tone mapping, gamut handling, or display/transfer encoding shows up as a pixel diff
// here even before dedicated HDR output exists. The example is input-driven and static
// in CI. Frame 300 (stable filename: `screenshot-300.png`) leaves headroom for the
// glTF scenes and environment maps to finish async loading.
(
    setup: (
        fixed_frame_time: Some(0.05),
    ),
    events: [
        (300, ScreenshotAndExit),
    ]
)
